OpenVPN Cookbook Chapter 3 sample code

The samples in this chapter are openvpn configuration files, 
as well as some helper scripts.

Chapter 3 is divided up into 8 recipes. Below is a list of which
configuration file is used in which recipe.

3.1 Simple configuration - non bridged
server: example3-1-server.conf
client: example3-1-client.conf

3.2 Enabling Client-to-Client traffic
server: example3-2-server.conf
client1: example3-2-client1.ovpn
client2: example3-2-client2.ovpn

3.3 Bridging - Linux
server: example3-3-server.conf
scripts: example3-3-bridge-start, example3-3-bridge-stop
client: example3-2-client2.ovpn

3.4 Bridging - Windows
server: example3-4-server.conf
client: example3-1-client.conf

3.5 Checking broadcast and non-IP traffic
server: example3-3-server.conf
scripts: example3-3-bridge-start, example3-3-bridge-stop
client: example3-2-client2.ovpn

3.6 External DHCP
server: example3-6-server.conf
client: example3-2-client2.ovpn

3.7 Using the status file
server: example3-7-server.conf
client: example3-1-client.conf

3.8 Management interface
server: example3-8-server.conf
client1: example3-1-client.conf
client2: example3-2-client2.ovpn

3.9 Integrating IPv6 into TAP-style networks
server: example3-9-server.conf
client: example3-1-client.conf

